VERSION 1.2
VERSION CHANGES

HOTFIX
Updated family luxury code to work after live change

CUMULATIVE CHANGES

ARCHETYPES
Schemer
  Reduced bonus orders per war to .5 (from 1)

UNITS + IMPROVEMENTS
Macemen
  Macemen now start with Cleave I and Anti-Infantry I (previously: Anti-Infantry I)
  Reduced cost to 90 training (from 100)
  Reduced cost to 125 iron (from 150)
  Reduced upkeep cost to 3 iron, 1 food (from 3 iron, 1 food, 1 training)
Holy Sites
  Disciple spawn rate increased to once every 10 years (previously: one every 20 years)
Museaum
  Reduced science multiplier to 1.33 (from 1.5)

EVENTS
Claimed Lands
  Added minimum t30 to event (from no turn limit)
Diegylis (Thracian elimination event)
  Removed from competitive mode
Local Authority (Influence mission event)
  Removed from competitive mode
Steed of the Gods (horse harvest event)
  Leader trait reward changed to equestrian (previously swift)
Sword of the Gods 
  Strength bonus changed to +25% (previously +50%) 
  Strength bonus changed to work vs all unit types (previously vs infantry only)

TECH AND TECH CARDS
Courtier tech cards changed
  Cost
    Reduced to 40% of tech cost (previously: 50%)
  Behavior
    Courtier tech cards now offer the player a choice of three set, previewable characters (previously: one random, not previewable)
  Locations
    Court Scholar Card moved to Land Consolidation (previously at Metaphysics)
    Court Scholar Card moved to Portcullis (previously at Scholarship)
    Court Soldier Card moved to Steel (previously at Battleline)
    Court Soldier Card moved to Composite Bow (previously at Infantry Square)
    Court Minister Card moved to Architecture (previously at Citizenship)
    Court Minister Card moved to Scholarship (previously at Jurisprudence)
    Court Merchant Card moved to Martial Code (previously at Fiscal Code)
    Court Merchant Card moved to Lateen Sail (previously at Chain Drive)
Luxury tech cards changed
  Behavior
    Luxury tech cards now offer the player the choice of any luxury desired by their families (previously: a set, non-family lux based on tree location)
